# pyramidalNumber

- _pyramidalNumber(r, n)_

Answer the _n_-th _r_-pyramidal number.

```
>>> 4.pyramidalNumber(23)
4324
```

Threads over lists,
calculate in turn the first few
triangular, square, pentagonal, hexagonal and heptagonal pyramidal numbers:

```
>>> 3.pyramidalNumber(1:9)
[1 4 10 20 35 56 84 120 165]

>>> 4.pyramidalNumber(1:9)
[1 5 14 30 55 91 140 204 285]

>>> 5.pyramidalNumber(1:9)
[1 6 18 40 75 126 196 288 405]

>>> 6.pyramidalNumber(1:9)
[1 7 22 50 95 161 252 372 525]

>>> 7.pyramidalNumber(1:9)
[1 8 26 60 115 196 308 456 645]
```

